<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="264" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[132,777,1204,1613]" box="[132,222,1204,1230]" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">REMARK</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[132,777,1204,1613]" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">
An obligate forest species in the Upper 
<collectingCountry box="[556,635,1236,1262]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and an indicator of intact forest. A recent phylogeographic study confirmed the identification of all four of our 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rochebrune" authorityYear="1885" box="[586,715,1299,1325]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Malacomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis box="[586,715,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">M. edwardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Apesokubi but showed that these 
<collectingRegion box="[510,655,1331,1357]" country="Ghana" name="Volta" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">Volta Region</collectingRegion>
specimens represent a lineage (F2) separate from the southwestern Ghanaian lineage (F1), “which may suggest the presence of multiple forest refugia” in 
<collectingCountry box="[410,482,1427,1453]" name="Ghana" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">Ghana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="BOHOUSSOU K. H. &amp; CORNETTE R. &amp; AKPATOU B. &amp; COLYN M. &amp; KERBIS PETERHANS J. &amp; KENNIS J. &amp; SUMBERA R. &amp; VERHEYEN E. &amp; N'GORAN E. &amp; KATUALA P. &amp; NICOLAS V." box="[497,761,1427,1454]" pageId="13" pageNumber="264" pagination="2049 - 2061" refId="ref17056" refString="BOHOUSSOU K. H., CORNETTE R., AKPATOU B., COLYN M., KERBIS PETERHANS J., KENNIS J., SUMBERA R., VERHEYEN E., N'GORAN E., KATUALA P. &amp; NICOLAS V. 2015. - The phylogeography of the rodent genus Malacomys suggests multiple Afrotropical Pleistocene lowland forest refugia. Journal of Biogeography 42: 2049 - 2061. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jbi. 12570" type="journal article" year="2015">
Bohoussou 
<emphasis box="[621,671,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">et al.</emphasis>
2015: 9
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="HURST J. &amp; BOWES LYON D. &amp; KEEFE E." box="[132,334,1459,1486]" pageId="13" pageNumber="264" refId="ref19603" refString="HURST J., BOWES LYON D. &amp; KEEFE E. O' 1995. - Kyabobo' 94: a joint Ghanaian and Oxford University Expedition. Final Report. KCP Publications, Ghana Wildlife Department, Institute for Renewable Natural Resources, 69 p." type="book" year="1995">
Hurst 
<emphasis box="[202,254,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">et al.</emphasis>
(1995)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 5 captures of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rochebrune" authorityYear="1885" box="[585,715,1459,1485]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Malacomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis box="[585,715,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">M. edwardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from moist semi-deciduous and secondary forest in KRNP which appears to be the only previous record of this species from the Ghana-Togo Highlands. We were not able to verify this species again at KRNP.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="264" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="13.[130,774,1636,1739]" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rochebrune" authorityYear="1885" box="[394,584,1636,1660]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Malacomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="264" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="edwardsi">
<emphasis box="[394,584,1636,1660]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">Malacomys edwardsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently listed as “Least Concern” on the IUCN Red List, but - already limited to the densest and best preserved forest in the 
<collectingRegion box="[492,614,1689,1713]" country="Ghana" name="Volta" pageId="13" pageNumber="264">Volta Region</collectingRegion>
- it would be one of the first rodent species to disappear with continued deforestation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
